festival.introText:
One of Britain’s most well known and well-loved festivals returns, Reading Festival 2023 promises to be bigger and better than ever before! 

Reading Festival boasts an ever impressive and diverse line-up, ranging all the way from punk and metal, through to rock, alternative, indie, dance, and electro; these are a few of the reasons why Reading Festival is so special.

Reading Festival has developed something of a habit of attracting some of the biggest global superstars, and world-beating bands on the planet to their Berkshire home. 2023 is set to be no different.

Music fans will also have a chance to see a whole host of new acts at Reading Festival this year including local bands in the smaller tents as well as the more established ones on Reading Festival's main stage. 

Reading Festival 2023 is set to be one of the most electrifying, and unforgettable festival experiences happening in Britain this year.
festival.descriptionText: Get more information about Reading Festival 2023 including festival tickets, news, reviews and lineups.

faqs.question: When is Reading Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Reading Festival returns to Richfield Avenue on Friday 25th - Sunday 27th August 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Reading Festival?
faqs.answer:
By car - Please follow the AA signage and directions on your car pass and not your Sat Nav. The car parks are located on grass fields, some with metal trackway approach roads and some internal roads are on land that may not be suitable for certain car suspensions.

 

By train -Reading train station is a 15-20 minute walk from the festival site. There are many routes from throughout the country to the station, including from London Paddington.

 

The last trains leaving Reading train station are often incredibly busy and do not run late on Friday and Saturday night. Please leave extra time if you're planning on using these services.

 

To check train times and service providers, please visit the National Rail website.

 

By coach - Reading Festival's exclusive coach travel partner Big Green Coach is the largest music festival coach provider in the UK and transport tens of thousands of people all over the country - so they really are the true experts! They will again be providing fantastic services from all over the UK direct to the Reading festival site. Use the Big Green Coach deposit scheme to secure your coach seat for just £10.

faqs.question: How much are Reading Festival tickets?
Does Reading have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: Yes, Reading Festival has on-site camping and you will be assigned your camping area when purchasing your tickets.

faqs.question: Where is Reading Festival?
faqs.answer: Reading Festival takes place at Richfield Avenue Festival site, Reading RG1 8EQ.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Reading Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
All ages are welcome at the festival. However, there are entry restrictions for under 16s and we do advise not bringing young children. Anyone 15 and under must be accompanied by a ticket holder over 18 years old at all times. Children under 13 years are admitted free. ID may be required upon entry to the event.

 

Please bring ID if you look under 21 years old and remember that legally there is no automatic right to be served alcohol. Service is always at the discretion of the licensee for whatever reason they decide, and the licensee is under no obligation to explain the reason.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Reading Festival?
faqs.answer:
The festival only allows sealed soft drinks under 500ml, as well as empty reusable plastic and metal bottles of any size into the Arena. Please refill your empty bottles at the water points inside the Arena for free.

 

Food is admitted for personal consumption only.
